        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 8:29PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 828 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 26
miles northwest of Nucla, or 30 miles northeast of La Sal, moving
north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation and
outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Mesa
County.

This includes Colorado 141 between mile markers 123 and 143.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
